RT.feature_notes: P denotes person record and H denotes housing record

SERIALNO.feature_notes: Use this column to link to the housing file. 7 digit number that contains leading zeros. Does not contain null values.

PUMA.feature_desc: Public use microdata area code (PUMA) based on 2010 Census definition
PUMA.feature_notes: Public use microdata areas (PUMAs) designate areas of 100,000 or more population. Use with ST for unique code. PUMAs are 5 digit numbers with leading zeros.

ST.feature_desc: State Code based on 2010 Census definitions
ST.feature_notes: State Code based on 2010 Census definitions. 2 digit number with leading zeros.

ADJINC.feature_desc: Adjustment factor for income and earnings dollar amounts (6 implied decimal places)
ADJINC.feature_notes: The value of ADJINC inflation-adjusts reported income to 2016 dollars. ADJINC applies to variables FINCP and HINCP in the housing record, and variables INTP, OIP, PAP, PERNP, PINCP, RETP, SEMP, SSIP, SSP, and WAGP in the person record. The number changes by year and is a 7 digit number where there are 6 implied decimal places. Float stored as object

AGEP.feature_notes: number up to 99 with 0 in tenths place

CITWP.feature_notes: 4 digit number representing the year stored as float instead of integer with a 0 in the tenths place

SSP.feature_notes: Use ADJINC to adjust SSP to constant dollars. Rounded to nearest hundreds and stored with 0 in tenths place.

WAGP.feature_desc: Wages or salary income past 12 months
